<li id="cite_note-83"><b><a href="#cite_ref-83" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFO.27Neill2008">O'Neill, Brendan (4 August 2008). <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/7540427.stm" class="external text" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/7540427.stm" rel="nofollow">"Do they really think the earth is flat?"</a>. BBC News Magazine<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/7540427.stm" class="external free" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/7540427.stm" rel="nofollow">http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/7540427.stm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-11-16</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Do+they+really+think+the+earth+is+flat%3F&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=O%27Neill&amp;rft.aufirst=Brendan&amp;rft.au=O%27Neill%2C+Brendan&amp;rft.date=4+August+2008&amp;rft.pub=BBC+News+Magazine&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F1%2Fhi%2Fmagazine%2F7540427.stm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Flat_Earth"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-84"><b><a href="#cite_ref-84" title="">^</a></b> Youssef M. Ibrahim, "Muslim Edicts Take on New Force", <i>New York Times</i>, February 12, 1995.</li>
<li id="cite_note-85"><b><a href="#cite_ref-85" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://binbaz.org.sa/RecDisplay.asp?f=n-04-1407-0300007.htm" class="external text" title="http://binbaz.org.sa/RecDisplay.asp?f=n-04-1407-0300007.htm" rel="nofollow">Audio recording of Ibn Baz</a> - Binbaz.org. Translation provided below.</li>
<li id="cite_note-86"><b><a href="#cite_ref-86" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://thetruereligion.org/modules/wfsection/article.php?articleid=258" class="external autonumber" title="http://thetruereligion.org/modules/wfsection/article.php?articleid=258" rel="nofollow">[17]</a><sup class="noprint Inline-Template"><span title="&#160;since November 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Dead_external_links" title="Wikipedia:Dead external links">dead link</a></i>]</span></sup></li>
<li id="cite_note-87"><b><a href="#cite_ref-87" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFShaykh">Shaykh, Ibn Baaz. <a href="http://www.fatwa-online.com/fataawa/miscellaneous/miscellaneous/0040819.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.fatwa-online.com/fataawa/miscellaneous/miscellaneous/0040819.htm" rel="nofollow">"Is the Earth round or flat?"</a>. fatwa-online.com<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.fatwa-online.com/fataawa/miscellaneous/miscellaneous/0040819.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.fatwa-online.com/fataawa/miscellaneous/miscellaneous/0040819.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.fatwa-online.com/fataawa/miscellaneous/miscellaneous/0040819.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-11-16</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Is+the+Earth+round+or+flat%3F&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Shaykh&amp;rft.aufirst=Ibn+Baaz&amp;rft.au=Shaykh%2C+Ibn+Baaz&amp;rft.pub=fatwa-online.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.fatwa-online.com%2Ffataawa%2Fmiscellaneous%2Fmiscellaneous%2F0040819.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Flat_Earth"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-88"><b><a href="#cite_ref-88" title="">^</a></b> Shaykh Bin Baz on the Roundness of the Earth (with Sound) on the Shaykhs website The audio is played automatically as the page is opened: <a href="http://binbaz.org.sa/RecDisplay.asp?f=n-04-1407-0300007.htm" class="external free" title="http://binbaz.org.sa/RecDisplay.asp?f=n-04-1407-0300007.htm" rel="nofollow">http://binbaz.org.sa/RecDisplay.asp?f=n-04-1407-0300007.htm</a> translated... -The question and answer was translated by Aqeel Walker, a former translator for Darussalam Publications in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia: Introduction: The following letter reached the program (broadcast program) from Kenya, sent by our brother, the student, Ibraheem Muhammad Al-Awwal. The brother says, "I heard the program Nurun 'alad-Darb (A Light upon the Path) and I benefited greatly from it. Therefore, I wanted to send these questions to you all because their topics are very perplexing to me. The first is: Is the earth round or flat?" Shaikh Bin Baz: According to the people knowledge (scholars of Islaam) the earth is round, for indeed Ibn Hazim and a group of other scholars mentioned that there is a consensus (unanimous agreement, Ijmaa') among the people of knowledge that it is round. This means that all of it is connected together thus making the form of the entire planet like a ball. However, Allaah has spread out surface for us and He has placed firm mountains upon it and placed the animals and the seas upon it as a mercy for us. For this reason, Allaah said: "And (do they not look) at the Earth, how it was made FLAT (Sutihat)." [Al-Ghaashiyyah (88):20] Therefore, it (the Earth) has been made flat for us in regards to its surface, so that people can live on it and so that people can be comfortable upon it. The fact that it is round does not prevent that its surface has been made flat. This is because something that is round and very large, if it is made flat (its surface), then its surface will become very vast or broad (i.e. having a flat appearance). Yes."</li>
</ol>
</div>


